The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                                 
	 New Delhi: Somdev Dev Varman and Harsh Mankad reached the doubles semi-finals of the $50,000 ATP Challenger event in the US with their respective partners after registering contrasting victories.    
	Somdev and the Philippines partner Treat Conard Huey stunned American third seeds Todd Widom and Michael Yani 6-3, 6-4 in their quarter final encounter. Mankad teamed up with American Scott Oudsema to overcome a first set lapse and beat Lestor Cook and Shane La Porte of the US 2-6, 6-2, 10-8 in their last-eight clash.        
	Frankfurt: Bayern Munich bosses have decided to part company with coach Juergen Klinsmann after the end of the season, a German newspaper said Friday.    
	However, should Bayern lose or draw Saturday at home against Eintracht Frankfurt in the Bundesliga, the newspaper said Klinsmann will be fired immediately, without citing any sources.        
	Manchester: Manchester United manager Alex Ferguson has defended the owning Glazer family with the Red Devils debt nearing $1 billion. Ferguson has never had any complaints about Malcolm Glazer, who took over United in 2005 and also owns the Tampa Bay Buccaneers, because he has been backed in the transfer market.          
	London: The administrators running ailing English Championship (second division) Southampton said on Thursday that 31 parties had expressed an interest in buying the club. The Saints parent company Southampton Leisure Holdings went into administration last week with reported debts of 27.5 million pounds.        
	New Delhi: A total prize money of Rs 15 lakh will be up for grabs for the top Indian athletes as the new season gets under way with three Grand Prix events next month. The first Grand Prix is scheduled for May 3 in Cochin followed by the second in Coimbatore on May 8 and third in Chennai on May 13.        
	New Delhi: Parupalli Kashyap won the first game against Bao Chunlai but could not finish it off and bowed out of the mens singles quarter finals at the Asian Badminton Championships at the Suwon stadium in South Korea Friday.        
	Mumbai: The International Federation of Bodybuilding and Fitness (IFBB) has suspended the Asian Bodybuilding Federation (ABBF) and its secretary general Paul Chua for allowing three dope-tainted body builders from Hong Kong to participate in the Doha Asian Games three years ago.        
	Jamshedpur: J.P. Singh, chief coach of Jharkhand Basketball Association (JBA), was Friday named head coach of the Indian womens basketball team for the 23rd FIBA Asian basketball championship, to be held at Taipei city from June 21 to 28.                                                                                                                                                                       
